</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wezloc>Wezloc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 1:57:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8613.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: From Developer's Corner: What's up</span><hr size=1> I am very happy with my class. I love my mage, and I am very happy with the progression the mage class is moving into.  I still feel that Mages are a very special class, and only those that love it, and play it well understand what the class should be. SOE doesn't really have a clue what mages, are or should be.<br>
<br>
What I mean is if mages are about Pets, and Bolts then why are we lacking in these areas. Yes FBoT is a great spell but why are there not more bolt spells? I really don't see why mages don't get fast cast bolts....Scars needs a serious upgrade, and so does char.  Well what i mean is we need some post lvl 60 upgrades to these spell lines. IMO these are serious balancing issues. Mages had fast cast nukes, althought weaker then wizard nukes, we still had them. Now we have large nukes which are great but we lack the variety we had before.<br>
<br>
The new pets are really not better then the epic pet. They only are the best option because the epic pet can not land spells on post 61+ mobs. So either the epic pet needs to be raised in level or the new pets need damage upgrades, and hit point upgrades. Pets die so fast it is a joke. If a mob is not slowed they are not even able to keep a mob at bay for 10secs. In the tier 2 and 3 planes so many mobs proc near unresistable dd nukes that even during enrage the pet is dying to procs. Pets get wasted in POP, and this is the first time ever that mage pets were useless in terms of tanking. Well mage pets were designed to tank. It is one of the balancing features of the class because we lack defensive spells. Well at this time our pets are not very good at taking damage, and there hps are insanely low. I think doubling there current hp total, and increasing there dps by 10-15 or increasing the proc rate on the summon weapons is the only way to fix the problem.<br>
<br>
Also Raz I can't even believe you tried to compare druid charm soloing to mage soloing. I will just not even comment on that anymore.  Just sit back, and think about why a mage can't even hold a candle to a druid soloing..............<br>
<br>
