Well my take on this is that SoE kinda sees the mage as a minor concern.  If you look at the numbers not many people play this class.<br>
<br>
So we got some nice damage in groups?  Still many a mage goes lfg for hours or days between groups.  We are almost completely unable to solo in PoP unless we have the ultra rare Call of the Arch Mage spell and do't mind a lot of deaths and risk in BoT.  Outside of that soloing for us at level 65 is just not possible unless 1 AA every few weeks is somehting you can live with.<br>
<br>
<br>
My Conclusion:<br>
<br>
SoE is not going to change the way the Mage can solo in PoP for the better.  In fact they will most likely nerf Mage Charm.<br>
<br>
I suggest all of you consider mages lucky to have some added group damage now.  Make a new character when the new expansion comes out.  Play your mage at raids.<br>
<br>
It was a good run of it.. but the class is not group desired and cannot solo well.  No one at SoE seems ot care.  /shrug.<br>
<br>
I'm happy enough to do good to great group damage on raids and those unlikely ocasions I get a mercy group.<br>
<br>
Outside of that I will simply make a froggy shaman and have some fun later in the year.  I play the game to have fun.. like many of you do or used to do.  Its not fun LFG for 4 hours.<br>
